/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I can't help you on the availability of FoL. I was given the spell by guildmates long ago; I think my copy dropped in PoG. <p>Marlowe Lawbringer<BR>
Crusader of Mithaniel Marr, Level 60 <BR>Innoruuk<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umarlowelawbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Marlowe Lawbringer</A> at: 4/19/02 9:02:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1567<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 10:12:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious: Flame of Light</span><hr size=1> Flame of light drops off Crystaline Shard Wurms in the wurm caves in Great Divide. A couple days of camping these should net you a copy or three.<br>
<br>
While I do not share Marlowes view of the spell as totally useless, I will say that it use is extremely limited, even moreso now that we have an inherent haste spell. As you gain better inherent haste and higher levels it does eventually become nearly useless.<br>
<br>
I used to load it as a damage booster in XP groups at 50-52 before I got haste and it helped at that time. I frankly never load it now though as my equipment has radically changed since that level so that I do a lot of damage. I now have to be careful of aggro in raid situations and need more mana to heal, so it use isn't what I need any more most of the time.<br>
<br>
But it does serve well when your dueling a caster with Run 3 and you have no run speed enhancements. You would be amazed how little they resist the spell and how few casts it can take to rip them up heheh.  <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>
Bertoxxulous Server<br>
<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>
Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaallyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taallyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/02 11:58:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Velious: Flame of Light</span><hr size=1> That would have to be embrassing for a caster ... to get nuked to death by a paladin ... ooohhh the shame <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'll load it up in Kael when I'm in a small group to pull with or to help with aggro control. Since the giants are immune to stun, it's got some use there.  It's a situational spell at best when you get it, and you'll get to the point that you could easily do the 125 pts of damage it does in one or two melee hits.<br>
<br>
Funny thing did happy with the spell once.  I was in a guild group in Kael, and we were faction hunting in the Manor since there wasn't a raid going on at the time.  A friend of our shaman tagged along and somehow recorded our fight in full motion video.  A couple of days later he posted a clip from the fight on his website.  The clip he chose had our group of 6 fighting 3 giants, the warrior and I was on one, the chanter charmed one, and the charmed giant was fighting the 3rd one. In the clip you see me casting Flame of Light and the one giant drops.  Hehe ... go pali nukes! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69612">Baron Taallyn Nifesblade</a><BR>
